        "short_description": "Efficiently deploy Red Hat OpenShift clusters on Virtual Private Cloud (VPC) pre-configured with AI capabilities and GPU-enabled clusters to accelerate machine learning workloads.",
        "long_description": "This automation streamlines the deployment of Red Hat OpenShift cluster on IBM Cloud with the OpenShift AI add-on. It accelerates the setup of machine learning environments by leveraging the capabilities of the OpenShift AI add-on on Virtual Private Cloud (VPC) infrastructure with GPU-enabled clusters, reducing the complexity of AI infrastructure management and allowing data scientists and developers to focus on model development and deployment. Learn more about [Red Hat OpenShift on IBM Cloud](https://cloud.ibm.com/docs/openshift?topic=openshift-getting-started) and the [OpenShift AI add-on](https://cloud.ibm.com/docs/openshift?topic=openshift-ai-addon-about). Refer [here](https://cloud.ibm.com/docs/containers?topic=containers-supported-cluster-addon-versions#openshift-ai-416) for supported AI addon versions.",
